4 HR____ MOURNING THE DEATH OF CALVIN MILLER II.
5
6 WHEREAS, it is with deep sorrow and regret that we
7 note the lamentable death of Calvin Miller II of Huntsville,
8 Alabama, on March 8, 2026, at the age of 76 years; and
9 WHEREAS, a native of Detroit, Michigan, Calvin Miller
10 II proudly served his country in the United States Army,
11 retiring with the rank of Sergeant First Class in April 1988
12 after more than 20 years of honorable and faithful service;
13 and
14 WHEREAS, following his military service, Mr. Miller
15 continued a life of leadership and service through his
16 extensive involvement in Freemasonry, beginning in
17 Huntsville where he became a member of Evening Star Lodge
18 No. 6 and was later initiated into the Ancient and Accepted
19 Scottish Rite of Freemansonry, Prince Hall Affiliation,
20 Southern Jurisdiction; and
21 WHEREAS, his dedication within the Masonic order led
22 to his elevation to the Honorary Thirty-Third Degree, and he
23 was later coroneted as a Sovereign Grand Inspector General
24 and made an Active Member of the United Supreme Council in
25 October 2003; he further served with distinction as Deputy
26 for the Orient of Alabama and as an Active Member until
27 October 2018; and
28 WHEREAS, Mr. Miller's leadership extended further
Page 1

WHEREAS, Mr. Miller's leadership extended further
HR274 INTRODUCED
29 through his service as Chair for the Committee on Class
30 Administration for the United States Supreme Council, where
31 he played a vital role in the preparation and advancement of
32 more than 2,500 Honorary Grand Inspectors General throughout
33 the Southern Jurisdiction; and
34 WHEREAS, he held numerous other Masonic distinguished
35 positions, including Past Master; Past Illustrious
36 Potentate; Past Patron; and Grand Worthy Patron for the
37 Mizpah Grand Chapter, Order of Eastern Star, Jurisdiction of
38 Alabama, where he faithfully served since 2014; and
39 WHEREAS, Mr. Miller was also a man of deep faith,
40 serving as an ordained Elder at Madkins Chapel Cumberland
41 Presbyterian Church in Huntsville; and
42 WHEREAS, he was a devoted husband to his wife,
43 Sherran; father of six adult children; and proud grandfather
44 of 12; his love for his family was evident in all that he
45 did; and
46 WHEREAS, Mr. Miller was a valued member of the
47 community and loved by many, and we join with others to
48 celebrate his life and to mourn his death; although his
49 presence will be greatly missed, his memory will be
50 cherished in the hearts and minds of those who were
51 fortunate to know him; now therefore,
52 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
53 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That the death of Calvin Miller II,
54 is recorded with deep sadness, and even as we mourn his
55 death, we also celebrate his life; this resolution is
